In this article, it is announced that June is declared African-American Music Appreciation Month by President Barack Obama. The article highlights the significant contributions of African-American musicians, composers, singers, and songwriters to American culture. It acknowledges the role of African-American music in expressing the hardships and aspirations of the community, as well as its ability to unite and inspire people. The article also mentions the various genres of African-American music, such as spirituals, rhythm and blues, jazz, blues, gospel, soul, rock and roll, and hip-hop. It emphasizes that African-American music continues to evolve and influence musical formats globally. The proclamation urges public officials, educators, and the American people to celebrate and appreciate African-American music through various activities and programs.